# GPU-fit tuning: Qwen3-Coder-Next 1M-context (YaRN) on Strix Halo.
#
# Pairs with models/qwen3-coder-next-1m.env (UD-Q5_K_M weights + YaRN x4).
#
# Memory math against the ~108 GiB GTT budget (validated per-token KV cost:
# 12 full-attention layers x 2 KV heads x 256 head_dim x (K+V) = 12,288
# elements/token; q8_0 ~= 1.0625 B/elem -> ~12.75 KiB/token; the 36 DeltaNet
# layers hold a constant F32 recurrent state, ~100 MiB total, ctx-independent):
#   weights (UD-Q5_K_M)              55.2 GiB
#   KV @ 1,048,576 tok, q8_0 K+V     12.8 GiB   (f16 would be 24 GiB -- also fits,
#                                                but stay q8_0 until A/B'd)
#   compute buffers @ ubatch 1024     ~4 GiB
#   DeltaNet recurrent state          ~0.1 GiB
#   ------------------------------------------
#   total                            ~72 GiB / 108 GiB GTT
#
# KNOWN RISK (unresolved upstream as of 2026-07-17): llama.cpp discussion
# #20000 reports repetition/hallucination with this model at ~80K+ context,
# suspected in the delta-net decay path. Run the long-context probe in the
# validation notes before trusting 1M output.
: "${CTX_SIZE:=1048576}"
